data.enText: a chemical element. Magnesium is a light, silver-white metal that burns with a bright white flame.

tr: a light silver-white ductile bivalent metallic element
in pure form it burns with brilliant white flame
occurs naturally only in combination (as in magnesite and dolomite and carnallite and spinel and olivine)

value.def: Magnesium is a light silvery-white metal which burns with a bright white flame.
